<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbbc69e4b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s2000g–3"><num value="2000g–3">§ 2000g–3.</num><heading> Reports to Congress</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Subject to the provisions of sections 2000a–4 and 2000g–2(b) of this title, the Director shall, on or before January 31 of each year, submit to the Congress a report of the activities of the Service during the preceding fiscal year.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbbc69e4c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/352/tX/s1004">Pub. L. 88–352, title X, § 1004</ref>, <date date="1964-07-02">July 2, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/267">78 Stat. 267</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
